name: (Taghbostan) A relic from the third century AD The period of the Sassanid dynasty
description: It is a collection of lithographs and lithographs of the Sassanid period that is located in Iran in Taghbestan neighborhood in the northeast of Kermanshah and in the west of Iran. This collection was built in the third century AD and has great artistic and historical value. Several historical scenes such as the coronation of Khosrow Parviz, the coronation of Ardeshir II, the coronation of Shahpour II and III, as well as several inscriptions (inscriptions) are engraved on the side of the inscriptions and the boar hunters' rites and playing music with musical instruments.
